nt curriculum.\par   Yale deepened its commitment to nonprofit management this year with\par the formation of a partnership with the Goldman Sachs Foundation. The\par foundation and the Pew Charitable Trusts donated $4.5 million to the\par partnership, which is starting a business-plan competition for\par nonprofit groups. The winners receive funding for their business\par ventures.\par   Other new projects at Yale include a research and teaching center to\par study corporate governance and a student-managed venture-capital fund\par that invests in start-ups in the New Haven, Conn., area.\par   Yale also offers concentrations in finance, strategy, marketing,\par leadership and operations management, with most graduates landing jobs\par in management consulting and financial services. Many M.B.A. students\par look beyond the management school and also take advantage of other\par parts of Yale University, such as the law school and the forestry and\par environmental studies school.\par   In The Wall Street Journal/Harris Interactive survey, recruiters\par rated Yale M.B.A. graduates as strong in teamwork, ability to drive\par results, analytical and problem-solving skills and awareness of\par \f28 \b \highlight22\uc2 \f2 corporate social\f28 \b0 \highlight\uc2 \f2 -\f28 \b \highlight22\uc2 \f2 responsibility\f28 \b0 \highlight\uc2 \f2  issues. Yale received lower ratings\par for students' entrepreneurial skills, the career-services office, the\par past acceptance rate for job offers and companies' ability to retain\par graduates they have hired.\par   The Recruiters Speak\par   -- The first thing that comes to mind about Yale\par   "Gregarious team players"\par   "Original perspective, out-of-the-box thinking"\par   "Do-gooders"\par   -- How Yale could improve its reputation\par   "Emphasize the hard skills"\par   "Publicize nonprofit orientation"\par   "Improve career-services department"\par   Yale on Yale\par   (Data provided by the Yale School of Management)\par M