ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 (c) 2002 The Financial Times Limited. All rights reserved \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 INSIDE TRACK - How to become good in all areas - \b \highlight22\uc2 CORPORATE SOCIAL RESPONSIBILITY\b0 \highlight\uc2  - CSR is here to stay - but it is unfamiliar territory for most managers.Alison Maitland reviews a guide for perp.\par \par \uc2 The presence of about 700 companies and 50 chief executives at the Johannesburg summit was further evidence that the business case for social responsibility has hit home.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Far fewer companies, however, are clear about how to manage what can be an amorphous collection of internal initiatives and external relationships on social, environmental and ethical issues.\par \par \uc2 The scandals in the US have underlined how "corporate responsibility taskforces" and codes of conduct are not enough on their own and can sometimes be a smokescreen. Probity and responsibility must be embedded in a company's culture, strategy and operations from the top down. But how can this be done? A new guide* from Business for Social Responsibility, a US non-profit research and advisory organisation with 1,400 member companies and affiliates, attempts to answer this by taking the reader step by step through the process of designing a \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  management system.\par \par \uc2 Only a handful of companies have a full CSR management system in place, says the organisation, which advises its members on how to make responsible practices integral to their strategy and oper-ations. Its corporate members, mainly in the US and Europe, have combined annual revenues of nearly $2,000bn ( \u163\'00\'A31,300bn) and employ 6m people. They include ABB, British Airways, Coca-Cola, Ikea, Unilever and Wal-Mart.\par \par \uc2 "Creating and building a successful CSR management system is a complex, long-term project for any company," says the report. "It involves a shift in the way a company conducts business and can be likened to implementing other large-scale change initiatives such as total quality management."\par \par \uc2 The guide runs through basics such as who currently has responsibility for CSR in the company, why a better management structure might improve things and what "hot-button" issues (child labour, drug pricing) face different sectors. It encourages companies to think hard about their stakeholders, what their concerns are, how credible and influential they are and whether they are a potential long-term partner or a liability.\par \par \uc2 Where the report is most thorough is in setting out and illustrating with examples the most common ways that companies assign responsibility for CSR at each level of management.\par \par \uc2 Boards, for example, may give responsibility to an existing director, appoint a new director with CSR expertise, create a dedicated committee or add CSR to the responsibilities of an existing committee, such as the audit or health and safety committee. Or the entire board may take responsibility.\par \par \uc2 Drawing on the experiences of its members, the report says that Ford's board deals with such issues through an \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  and public policy committee led by the company's chairman. At Pfizer, the full board takes decisions on CSR and periodically reviews the company's policies and practices.\par \par \uc2 The same five options exist at executive committee level as at board level. For example, Novartis assigns formal responsibility for CSR issues jointly to the heads of legal and general affairs and of human resources, who sit on the executive committee.\par \par \uc2 At senior management level, the question is whether to centralise or decentralise. British Telecommunications has combined its environmental, social and community programmes into a single social policy unit, in part to encourage a strong culture of social responsibility across its autonomous business units. At Cisco, on the other hand, responsibility is shared between the human resources, legal affairs and workplace resources departments, each with staff worldwide who devote some of their time to CSR. The company believes that giving business units the freedom to determine most CSR policies and practices themselves makes them more successful.\par \par \uc2 If CSR can be described as a management discipline, this wide variety of models demonstrates how young and evolving it is. Which models work best? That depends on the company, how it is organised and what issues it faces, the report says. This is not a "one size fits all" exercise. There are, however, some pointers:\par \par \uc2 Hiring an outsider may plug a gap in expertise but can create other problems if the expert has an insufficient grasp of the company's culture and operations.\par \par \uc2 Adequate training is critical for managers and staff with CSR responsibilities, especially those whose original job descriptions have been expanded to take on this new area.\par \par \uc2 Some companies are training and educating all their board directors, which sounds sensible, not just in the light of Enron and WorldCom. "Many stakeholders expect directors to be knowledgeable about the full range of social, environmental and financial issues that affect the companies on whose boards they serve and to be proactive in how they address them," says the report.\par \par \uc2 Whether a company centralises or decentralises responsibility, it must build mechanisms for communication between departments and business units. Cross-functional teams play an important part in integrating CSR and encouraging feedback from supporters and sceptics. At DuPont, a "corporate environmental business council", chaired by the chief executive and comprising senior executives from investor relations, corporate planning, finance and technology, meets twice or three times a year to discuss big issues such as climate change and the United Nations Global Compact.\par \par \uc2 This is a topical guide that asks many useful questions. It is, perhaps inevitably, short on concrete answers. Companies have only just begun to measure the impact of their CSR activities. However, more detailed case studies, including commentary from executives on the lessons they have learnt, would help others to determine which model is best for them.\par \par \uc2 * Designing a CSR Structure, available from {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.bsr.org/store"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 www.bsr.org/store}}}\par \par \uc2 Further articles are available at {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.ft.com/csr"}}{\fldrslt{\cf2 \uc2 www.ft.com/csr}}}\par \par \uc2 London Edition 1. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 ccat : \uc2 Corporate/Industrial News | ccsr : \uc2 Corporate Social Responsibility\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RE\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 eecz : \uc2 European Union Countries | eurz : \uc2 Europe | uk : \uc2 United Kingdom | weurz : \uc2 Western Europe\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IPC\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 London Edition 1 | INSIDE TRACK | Company News | Corporate Governance | Society &Social Affairs | United Kingdom | European Union | Europe | Western Europe\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\asp