aph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 (c) 2002 The Financial Times Limited. All rights reserved \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Business is expected toplay a "pivotal role" inmeeting the goals laid down atthis summer's World Summit on Sustainable Development, the government will say today.\par \par \uc2 Michael Meacher, \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  minister, says there are "immediate and long-term implications for business" from several of the summit's commitments, such as the promotion of sustainable production and \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 .\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The government is considering a raft of measures, including changes to environmental regulations and taxes, in an effort to improve the sustainability of the business sector. "The contribution of business will be heavily influenced by the quality of government intervention," Mr Meacher will say at a conference organised today by Demos, the left-leaning think-tank.\par \par \uc2 But the environmental community is sceptical about the government's determination to change business practices.\par \par \uc2 Jonathan Porritt, chairman of the Sustainable Development Commission, said: "Although I think the government's heart is in the right place, they don't really think it through in a systematic and strategic way.\par \par \uc2 "There is still a sense that regulating for things to happen is business-unfriendly."\par \par \uc2 Becky Willis, director of the Green Alliance, a think-tank, believes the central problem is a lack of leadership in pushing the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  agenda across government. "The prime minister is doing well on the international stage but he is not really taking a lead on the domestic agenda."\par \par \uc2 Mr Meacher will criticise the tax regimes and regulatory frameworks established by previous governments for impeding sustainable development. "In the past what was good for business has too often been harmful to the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 . We need to change that."\par \par \uc2 A Treasury review of environmental taxation, which will set out additional measures to discourage waste and reward efficiency, is due to be published alongside the forthcoming pre-Budget report. At the same time, the strategy unit is due to publish a report on measures to tackle waste.\par \par \uc2 The government is also planning changes to environmental regulations that will increase the scrutiny on polluting companies, reduce costs for better performers, improve stakeholder consultation and simplify applications and licences.\par \par \uc2 The Department for \b \highlight22\uc2 Environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 , Food and Rural Affairs is developing a strategy for "modernising" environmental regulations with the \b \highlight22\uc2 Environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  Agency designed to improve the co-ordination between the different regulatory regimes, while minimising the overall regulatory burden.\par \par \uc2 Mr Meacher will emphasise the importance of partnerships between governments, non-governmental organisations and business.\par \par \uc2 London Edition 2. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b NS\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 gcat : \uc2 Political/General News | genv : \uc2 Environmental News\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b RE\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 eecz : \uc2 European Union Countries | eurz : \uc2 Europe | uk : \uc2 United Kingdom | weurz : \uc2 Western Europe\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\