trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 (c) 2003 The Financial Times Limited. All rights reserved \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 From Mr Rob Lake.\par \par \uc2 Sir, The Higgs review of the role of non-executive directors makes important recommendations to strengthen their monitoring function, increase their skills and broaden the "gene pool" from which they are drawn. But it does not go far enough to address adequately the host of social responsibility and ethical issues facing companies today. Boards that fail to address effectively the particular challenges in this arena facing their business may cost the company and its investors dear through direct factors such as increased costs or damage to vital intangible assets such as reputation.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The familiar twin pillars of corporate governance apply here - board structures, and the quality of the people in those structures. Only a handful of companies have a specialist board committee on the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  or \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  (CSR). But providing a focus for the issues in this way is clearly good practice. All FTSE 350 companies should think hard about whether to emulate it.\par \par \uc2 The Higgs review's proposals to cast the net for non-execs more widely are very welcome. People with senior business experience in specialist functions such as the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2 , or from voluntary sector organisations specialising in CSR, can bring both technical understanding and an appreciation of the outside world's view of important issues facing the company. The number of people from these backgrounds currently on British boards is minute. Companies should seek out such people and embrace the expertise and challenge they will bring.\par \par \uc2 Excellence in CSR is likely to be an increasingly important success factor for companies. Setting up a committee does not solve a problem, but at least it provides a guarantee that it will be discussed. Putting people on the committee with expertise, energy and outside perspectives will help still further.\par \par \uc2 Rob Lake, Head of SRI Engagement and Corporate Governance, Henderson Global Investors, London EC2M 2DA\par \par \uc2 London Edition 2. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\