\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CY\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 (c) 2003 The Financial Times Limited. All rights reserved \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Sybil the receptionist may greet you when you arrive at the privately-run Seaview hotel and restaurant. But that is as far as you can take any comparisons with television's Fawlty Towers.\par \par \uc2 For Nicky Hayward, part of the husband and wife team that owns and manages the Seaview, is adamantly and actively engaged in ridding the industry of the image of amateurish incompetence created by John Cleese's 1970s sitcom.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 Seaview, on the Isle of Wight, is run on entirely different lines, with a feeling of \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  strongly at the core of its identity. It also offers positive proof that a professional and principled approach can be a viable route to success.\par \par \uc2 "We believe in fully involving our staff and contributing to the local community," says Mrs Hayward It has won her and husband Nick a Queens Award for sustainable development.\par \par \uc2 Formal and informal training and involving their people to a high level has won management Quality and IIP recognition.\par \par \uc2 "But the practical results of better people are higher standards of service, in an industry where service is all. We don't suffer the shortage of skills or high staff turnover that is the industry norm," says Mrs Hayward.\par \par \uc2 The Haywards have also taken on disadvantaged young people as part of modern apprentices programmes, allowing them to train and qualify as chefs. All staff are encouraged to gain vocational qualifications.\par \par \uc2 A policy of sourcing all produce from local fishermen and farmers also pays dividends. "Buying our milk and dairy produce from the local farmer may cost more, but quality is assured and when he wants to take his wife out, they come to our restaurant.\par \par \uc2 "When we took over 23 years ago, trade was very seasonal. Now it is spread more evenly through the year, with a high proportion coming from locals." The hotel, restaurant and pub, in Seaview, near Ryde, derives its \u163\'00\'A31.2m turnover in roughly equal thirds from accommodation, food and the two bars.\par \par \uc2 The 16 rooms cost between \u163\'00\'A370 and \u163\'00\'A3140 a night, including breakfast, while the restaurant, which now employs eight chefs where Mrs Hayward once cooked alone, boasts a number of good food awards.\par \par \uc2 Her favourite dishes remain the summer pudding made from tomatoes she devised to help a local growers co-operative, and a hot crab ramekin.\par \par \uc2 Both Haywards are hotel professionals; he was manager of the Athenaeum in Piccadilly, while she was born and brought up at another hotel on the island. Nicky Hayward was awarded the MBE for her work for local organisations, and for contributions to national industry training and tourist bodies.\par \par \uc2 She claims that finding the time for these activities depends on a management structure that devolves much of the day-to-day running to the 40 staff. "We have a meeting for 90 minutes every Friday morning, where we go through the budgets for the week and other details. The staff are organised in five groups - beds, bars, kitchens, housekeeping and the office.\par \par \uc2 "Everyone has the chance to say what they want, and the staff decide their own salaries based on what they think the business can afford."\par \par \uc2 The \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  is also important, with as much recycled as possible. And guests are encouraged to use environmentally-friendly transport. "Those who arrive by yacht are especially welcome," she adds.\par \par \uc2 1. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 i66 : \uc2 Hotels/Restaurants/Casinos | i665 : \uc2 Lodgings | i6651 : \uc2 Hotels (except Casino)/Motels\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b