aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 National Poetry Day is due to be celebrated in some style in the unlikely \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  of Unilever's ice-cream and frozen food division this autumn.\par \par \uc2 Three poets will be invited into the workplace to read from their work, and a new poetry section is to be opened in the library in the staff restaurant.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The event will be monitored by the company's reading group, which meets once a month in work time to discuss themes raised by their reading material - leadership, communication, relationships.\par \par \uc2 It is not the first time the company has dabbled with the written word - last year Jackie Wills, a poet-in-residence, attended a series of meetings on the development of a fabric conditioner and wrote poems about her experience. Employees were then invited to express their own views using poetic imagery.\par \par \uc2 The Unilever initiative is typical of the way the relationship between business and the arts is changing. Companies that used to be content to give money to arts organisations out of altruism, or because the chairman's wife loved going to the ballet, are looking for more sophisticated sponsorship relationships.\par \par \uc2 "Many sponsorships were set up because businesses just believed it was 'a good thing' to support the arts, and it was an ideal way to entertain their clients for the evening," said Jonathan Tuchner of Arts &Business, the organisation that brings the two worlds together.\par \par \uc2 "That still happens to some extent but the relationship has changed. Businesses now want to know what the arts have got to offer them in terms of creativity, innovation and ideas. And they are not doing it for philanthropic reasons - they do it because it makes them better at business."\par \par \uc2 Arts &Business's latest figures show arts sponsorship has been holding its own. Although investment in the arts fell to GBP111m in 2001-02 compared with the high of GBP150.4m in 1999-2000, that figure was inflated by millennium capital projects, which at GBP45.7m accounted for nearly a third of the global sum.\par \par \uc2 "It has held up pretty well, but there has been much more emphasis on how businesses can embed the arts into their working practices," said Mr Tuchner.\par \par \uc2 James Hill, chairman of Unilever's ice-cream and frozen foods division, who was responsible for the company's Project Catalyst, which brings artists and writers into the workplace, said the scheme was justified in hard-headed business terms.\par \par \uc2 He said: "We are in the business of branded consumer goods, and we believe bringing art and design skills into our \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  helps us in advertising, marketing, new product development, and gives us an advantage over our competitors."\par \par \uc2 He said another reason for the initiative was that it helped to retain and attract staff. "People have a more complex motivational set than in the past, and they like to feel that they are part of something worthwhile, and growing as individuals."\par \par \uc2 In return, staff at Unilever help arts organisations with the more "prosaic" skills of profit and loss accounting and cost-benefit analysis, said Mr Hill, who mentors an employee from the National Theatre, and sits on its board.\par \par \uc2 Mr Tuchner said support for the arts also increasingly came under companies' \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2  profile. "Helping the arts contributes to creating a better \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  for the whole community, and that is something else which attracts people. There is evidence that people move to areas that are seen as culturally dynamic."\par \par \uc2 Some companies still prefer to make a bigger splash with their arts sponsorship. YTL, the Malaysian company that bought Wessex Water last year, reportedly paid GBP3m to bring the Three Tenors to Bath this month.\par \par \uc2 "The business generated for Bath and the goodwill YTL gained from its residents was worth much more," says the YTL community web site. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CO\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 ulvr : \uc2 Unilever PLC | unifl : \uc2 Unilever NV\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ad