spnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b LP\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 As the latest big business scandal unfolds at Parmalat, the Italian dairy group, it seems appropriate that this year's survey should examine the ingredients of corporate reputation more closely than ever.\par \par \uc2 Chief executives, as well as commentators from campaign groups and the media, have been asked for the first time to nominate the companies they rate most highly for governance and social responsibility. They have also been questioned, for the second consecutive year, on which companies demonstrate the greatest integrity.\par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b TD\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \uc2 The United States, which produced the Sarbanes-Oxley legislation after its devastating corporate scandals, is also home to many of the companies that score most highly for governance and integrity. Japanese companies, too, figure prominently in the top 20 on governance, integrity and social responsibility.\par \par \uc2 Four companies - General Electric, Microsoft, Toyota and IBM - dominate the top positions for all three measures of reputation. They are also the world's most respected companies.\par \par \uc2 The survey shows there is a big overlap in definitions of integrity, responsibility and good governance. Chief executives regard honest and ethical behaviour, strong leadership and a positive corporate culture as the main ingredients of good governance. GE, which heads the governance league, is "very open regarding how much directors are paid", says one CEO. Others praise GE's succession planning and the independence and stability of its board.\par \par \uc2 Good governance does not invariably equate with high levels of respect, however. Bayer, Deutsche Bank and Marks and Spencer, for example, figure among the top 50 for corporate governance but not the 50 most respected companies. On the other hand, Disney, Honda, Johnson &Johnson and Southwest Airlines are among the 50 most respected companies but do not make the good governance league.\par \par \uc2 Ford and BP feature in both but score far more highly for governance than respect. Ford, which comes in 8th place on corporate governance compared with 36th in the most respected league, is "well-managed at all stages" and has "good leadership", according to the chief executives. BP, in 11th place for governance, has "strong ethics", a "superb CEO" and "cares about diversity and competence".\par \par \uc2 Credit Suisse is the one company nominated by NGO and media commentators, but not chief executives, for good governance. However, no explanations were given for this particular nomination.\par \par \uc2 In previous years, respondents have been asked about companies' environmental record or their likely social and economic impact on emerging markets. This time they were asked which companies best demonstrate their commitment to \b \highlight22\uc2 corporate social responsibility\b0 \highlight\uc2 , which includes social, environmental and ethical behaviour.\par \par \uc2 Here there are greater differences between the nominations of chief executives and of media and NGO representatives. The companies that make a splash with campaigners and journalists include Campbell Soup, Ikea and DaimlerChrysler, none of which figure in the top 20 chosen by chief executives.\par \par \uc2 This may be because the two groups differ in their understanding of what constitutes social responsibility. Chief executives are most likely to say they have nominated a company because it is "socially and ethically responsible". Other reasons they give are having a clear strategy on the \b \highlight22\uc2 environment\b0 \highlight\uc2  and helping charities and the community. NGOs and the media have picked companies predominantly for their charitable and community activities and for investing in staff and training.\par \par \uc2 Another curious finding is that ExxonMobil, the US oil group with which Greenpeace has battled over climate change, comes 22nd in the CEOs' list of social ly responsible companies.\par \par \uc2 BP, Honda, Royal Dutch/Shell and Ford all achieve higher scores for social responsibility than for respect. On the other hand, Wal-Mart, the world's fifth most respected company, achieves only 16th place for social responsibility. Dell, the world's seventh most respected company, only manages 28th place for governance and 17th for integrity. It does not feature in the league of socially responsible companies.\par \par \uc2 Several companies score far better for integrity this year than last, when this question was included in the survey for the first time. Johnson &Johnson, which moves from 20th to fifth place, wins praise for transparency and good crisis management. "It does not hide problems", says one respondent. Another says it puts customers' interests before short-term profits.\par \par \uc2 Berkshire Hathaway, rising from 21st to sixth place, is cited for transparency, for going "against the political climate", and for "sorting problems out well". DuPont, which soars from 36th to ninth place, is "ethical, above board and not devious", says one chief executive. Another cites "its ability to set high standards of marketing".\par \par \uc2 Both chief executives and campaign groups agree that integrity is chiefly about being honest, ethical, socially responsible and respectable, all of which are reflected in a good reputation. However, a few companies such as 3M, Southwest Airlines and Cisco Systems appear in the most respected list but not the integrity list. The Body Shop scores on integrity but not respect.\par \par \uc2 Companies that score less well for integrity this year include Wal-Mart, Coca-Cola, Procter &Gamble and BMW. Mercedes, Renault, McDonald's and Virgin have dropped out of the table altogether. \par \cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b CO\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 cenord : \uc2 Parmalat SpA\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\pard \qr \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 \b IN\b0\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 i41 : \uc2 Food/Beverages/Tobacco | i413 : \uc2 Dairy Products | ifood : \uc2 Food Products\cell \pard \ql \li0\ri0\widctlpar\intbl\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0 {  \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx720\clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-15 \cellx9360\row} \trowd\trgaph15\trqc\trleft-15 \clvertalt\clpadl15\clpadr-1